The com.atlassian.confluence.content.render.xhtml.view.ViewHeadingFragmentTransformer class does not respect the fact that some heading tags may already have an ID associated with them.

So for the storage-format
{code}
<h1 id="title-heading" class="pagetitle with-breadcrumbs">
{code}

The ViewHeadingFragmentTransformer will generate
{code}
<h1 id="page.user-logopage.breadcrumbspage.title-text-span" id="title-heading" class="pagetitle with-breadcrumbs">
{code}

Obviously this is incorrect and should be avoided.

This should be resolvable by adding the following at line 59 in the FragmentTransformer
{code}
            if (startElement.getAttributeByName(new QName(XhtmlConstants.XHTML_NAMESPACE_URI, "id"))==null) { 
{code}

It's probably worth checking the other FragmentTransformers for similar issues.

